---
description: Load an nTasker task into the session for processing
---

# nTasker task #$ARGUMENTS (via /{COMMAND_NAME})

Your first action: run the loader below with your shell tool. It prints the
task (title, description, project, phase, priority) and moves it to
phase "wip" (In Progress):

    python3 {HELPER_PATH} "$ARGUMENTS"

Then work the task:

1. Read the loaded task data.
2. Make sure you are in the right project directory. If the loader printed a
   project-mismatch warning, stop and ask the user whether to proceed here or
   switch -- do not start work until they confirm.
3. On unclear requirements, ask -- do not assume.
4. When your work is done, hand it off to review by moving the task to
   phase "review" (this is a handoff, not a close -- no user OK needed):

       ntasker patch "$ARGUMENTS" --phase review

   If you could not finish (blocker, missing info, failed verification), do
   NOT move to review -- leave the phase as-is and report the blocker.

**Hard rules:**

- Never set status=done on your own. Closing a task is the user's decision;
  only do it when the user explicitly asks (then: ntasker done "$ARGUMENTS").
- The only autonomous tracker writes allowed are phase "wip" on start (done by
  the loader) and phase "review" when you genuinely finished. Nothing else.
- Never archive on someone's behalf. No new tasks, no deletes, no writes to
  other task IDs.
